# Clerk Authentication Configuration
# Follow setup instructions at: https://clerk.com

# ============================================
# STEP 1: Create Clerk Account & Application
# ============================================
# 1. Go to https://clerk.com and sign up
# 2. Create new application: "Hook Line Studio"
# 3. Enable authentication methods:
#    ✓ Email/Password
#    ✓ Google OAuth
#    ✓ GitHub OAuth (optional)

# ============================================
# STEP 2: Get API Keys from Clerk Dashboard
# ============================================
# Navigate to: API Keys section in Clerk dashboard
# Copy these values:

# Frontend - Publishable Key (starts with pk_)
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_publishable_key_here

# Backend - Secret Key (starts with sk_)
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here

# Webhook - Secret for signature verification (starts with whsec_)
# Get from: Webhooks section after creating webhook endpoint
CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_your_webhook_secret_here

# ============================================
# STEP 3: Configure Redirect URLs
# ============================================
# These tell Clerk where to redirect after auth actions

# Sign in/up pages
VITE_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
VITE_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up

# Post-authentication redirects
VITE_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=/app
VITE_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=/onboarding

# Fallback URL
VITE_CLERK_FALLBACK_REDIRECT_URL=/app

# ============================================
# STEP 4: Configure Clerk Dashboard Settings
# ============================================
# In Clerk Dashboard → Settings → Paths:
# - Add redirect URLs above
# - Set home URL: http://localhost:5173 (dev) or your production URL

# In Clerk Dashboard → Settings → Restrictions:
# - Enable email verification (recommended)
# - Set password requirements

# In Clerk Dashboard → Webhooks:
# - Create endpoint: http://localhost:3000/api/webhooks/clerk (dev)
# - Subscribe to events: user.created, user.updated, user.deleted
# - Copy webhook secret to CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET above

# ============================================
# STEP 5: Copy to .env
# ============================================
# Once you have your keys:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Replace placeholder values with actual keys
# 3. Never commit .env to git (already in .gitignore)

# ============================================
# Optional: Clerk Features
# ============================================
# Customize appearance in Clerk Dashboard → Customization:
# - Logo, colors, branding
# - Social login buttons
# - Email templates
# - Session duration

# ============================================
# Production Environment Variables
# ============================================
# For production deployment, update these in:
# - Vercel: Project Settings → Environment Variables
# - Railway: Project → Variables
# - Use pk_live_* and sk_live_* keys (not pk_test_*)
